How to run the program:
-----------------------
-The entry point to the program is: nbc.py.
-This can be invoked from commandline as instructed in the assignment.
-nbc.py is a wrapper module which reads in input files, creates appropriate data structures and pass to the function in NBCOnSets.py module which has the actual logic of NBC Classifier.

The program will print an error message and exit under following conditions:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Fully biased sample is provided as training set. (i.e: class labels take only one value for all instances)
2. Undefined classification task provided. (i.e: task!=5 and task!=7)
3. Not sufficient unique words in the given training set. (i.e: at least there should be 2200 unique words to build the features.)
